-- SocGen starts action against rogue trader
-- 
-- Thu Jan 24, 2008 6:04am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/24/us-socgen-whereabouts-idUSNPAC00917220080124

 

 PARIS  (Reuters) - Societe Generale said on Thursday it was starting legal action against the rogue trader whose alleged fraud cost it 4.9 billion euros. 

 "A complaint is being lodged," SocGen Chairman Daniel Bouton told a press conference. Asked if he knew where the trader was, Bouton replied: "I don't know where he is." (Reporting by  Sudip Kar-Gupta )